A total of 42,551 transcripts sequences were obtained from the NGS analysis of all four tail tissue samples. All the sequences were obtained from a total of ~ 30 million reads from each sample. De novo and functional annotation yielded 39,953 transcripts with highest similarity with 
 Gekko japonicas (41.3%) and no blast hit (49%) to any reptilian database. The transcripts were submitted to NCBI and obtained accession number (SUB6743288 & PRJNA587566; 
 https://dataview.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/object/PRJNA587566). The transcripts were further translated to obtain the protein sequence database for proteomic analysis.
